\# Set-up

```{r setup}
library(tidyverse)
library(here)
library(ggridges)
```

# Data Context

```{r data}
surveys <- read_csv(here("surveys.csv"))
```

\# Initializing Variables

```{r variables}
weight <- surveys$weight
ftlength <- surveys$hindfoot_length
species <- surveys$species
```

\### \*\*Prompt\*\*

1\) Medium - Ridge Plots

For this challenge you are to change the plot you created in question 13 (or 14) to a ridge plots. You will need to instacarll the ggridges package and explore the geom_density_ridges() function.

# Lab 2 Question 13

```{r plot}
ggplot(data = surveys, 
       mapping = aes(x = weight,
                    y = species)) +
  geom_jitter(color = "tomato") +
  geom_boxplot(outlier.shape = NA) +
  labs(title = "Distribution of Weight Within Each Species",
       x = "Weight (g)",
       y = "Species")  
```

# Challenge 2

```{r challenge}
ggplot(data = surveys, 
       mapping = aes(x = weight,
                    y = species)) +
  geom_jitter(color = "tomato") +
  geom_density_ridges() +
  labs(title = "Distribution of Weight Within Each Species",
       x = "Weight (g)",
       y = "Species")  
```
